description.narrative:
(1)A new model of meaningful engagement with CSOs is created;
(2)Number of capacity  building for institutions in East Jerusalem ;
(3) Quality and quantity of CSOs services increased.
(4) Linkages between different institutions enhanced; 
(5) Different synergies and dialogues are created.

comment.narrative:
(1) Political complexity resulting from occupation and no model of engagement with CSOs;
(2)Limited capacity for the institutions in East Jerusalem;  
(3)Weak and fragmented services; 
(4)Lack of linkages between the different institutions; 
(5)Limited synergies and dialogue among CSOs.

description.narrative:
1. All health  education personnel in Gaza hired before and after 2007 are either reintegrated into the official payroll or are provided with alternatives, based on clearly defined and transparent criteria and options. 
2. Existence of a coordination mechanism of the civil society and popular initiatives to promote reconciliation. 
3. Number of national events organized to support national reconciliation and federate efforts;
4. Existence of an independent monitoring mechanism for the implementation of the reconciliation agreements;
5. Existence of an area-based recovery strategy for the Gaza Strip.

comment.narrative:
1. A rough estimate of the potential costs of the civil service integration is provided to the Prime Ministers Office; 
2. An operational action plan clarifying the sequences of the reintegration process is developed; 
3. An open dialogue on the options for civil service reintegration is initiated with the stakeholders. 
4. Mapping of the civil society initiatives promoting national reconciliation; 
5. Four events promoting national unity organized to strengthen the interaction between CSOs and enhance public support to national unity; Development of a social cohesion measurement tool.
7. Support Civil society networks to promote reconciliation and national unity; Inclusive civil society monitoring mechanism for reconciliation established;
8. An area-based recovery strategy and action plan completed.
